FBIS4-39335 "drsov109_e_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs DPRK Minister Calls for Talks With ROK on Nuclear Issue DPRK Minister Calls for Talks With ROK on Nuclear Issue LD0606163494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1521 GMT 6 Jun 94 LD0606163494 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] North Korea rejects pressure as a tool to solve the nuclear problem of the peninsula. Its Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam said so in Ukraine where he arrived on 6 June. He said that direct talks with Seoul were the only way to have the problem solved and that North Korea wanted to make the Korean peninsula a nuclear-free zone. Kim Yong-nam expressed the hope that the third round of talks between Pyongyang and Seoul would bring about positive results in that field. He welcomed Ukraine's desire to become a nonnuclear country. Kim Yong-nam and his Ukrainian counterpart Anatoliy Zlenko will have talks Monday afternoon.
